---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Letter Guides — Words by Starting Letter, Ending & Containing"
  description="136 Scrabble word guides organised by letter. Words starting with A-Z, words ending with vowels and high-value letters, and letter pair combinations. Free, no signup."
  keywords="scrabble words starting with, words ending with, words containing, letter guides scrabble, scrabble words by letter, word lists by letter"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How can I find Scrabble words that start with a specific letter?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our letter guides cover every letter A-Z with curated lists of the best Scrabble words starting with that letter. Each guide includes high-scoring picks, common plays, and strategic notes for using that letter effectively on the board." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why are words containing specific letter pairs useful in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Letter pair guides help you spot words when you have two specific letters on your rack. For example, knowing words containing QU, XY, or ZZ helps you play those tiles together instead of struggling to use them separately. This is especially useful for awkward combinations." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which letters are hardest to use in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Q (without U), V, W, and C are the most difficult tiles. Q has very few valid words without U. V and W have limited short-word options. C often needs common letters like H or K to form useful words. Our guides for these letters provide comprehensive word lists to overcome these challenges." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1">
      <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
      <span class="mx-1">›</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">Letter Guides</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Letter Guides</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-4">
      136 guides covering words organised by letter position. Find the best Scrabble words starting with any letter A-Z, 
      words ending with vowels and high-value consonants, and words containing specific letter pairs. 
      The ultimate reference for rack-specific word finding.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-400 mb-8">
      When you draw your tiles, the first question is always "what can I make with these letters?" These guides answer that question for every starting letter, ending letter, and difficult letter combination in Scrabble. Each guide lists the highest-scoring words available, explains which words appear in both SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries, and suggests strategic plays for specific rack scenarios. The "Words Starting With" series (A-Z) covers the best openers and extensions for each letter. The "Words Ending With" guides help you find words that hook onto existing plays on the board. And the "Words Containing" series tackles the hardest letter combinations — Q without U, double letters, unusual pairings like AA, QI, and ZO that casual players never learn. Bookmark the guides for your weakest letters and study 5 new words per day — within a month you'll have hundreds of new scoring options.
    </p>

